---
title: One-Pot Turkey, Cauliflower & Bean Soup with Cilantro & Blue Corn Tortilla Chips
description: This hearty, flavorful vegan soup is ready in under 30 minutes and cooks in one pot, making cleanup a breeze! Cauliflower and beans are simmered in a richly-spiced broth—veggie stock, onion, green pepper, tomatoes, and Southwest seasonings—until tender. Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve crunchy blue corn tortilla chips alongside for a SOUP-er supper.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/63cff91e76cb79a262086eae-90c38e09.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64f8dbb5d6d437ce24b89ced.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: Mexican
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 87 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 45 g
  fiber: 17 g
  sodium: 2540 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-turkey-cauliflower-bean-soup-64f8dbb5d6d437ce24b89ced
time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced). Core, deseed, and finely dice @long green pepper{1}(deseeded and finely diced). Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces) into ½-inch pieces. Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} (large pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of oil. Stir in @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon}, diced tomato, and @tomato paste{1}(1 unit); cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Once veggies are slightly softened, 2-3 minutes, add @ground turkey{10%ounce} to pot. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Cook through the rest of the step as instructed.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Stir @black beans{1%unit} and their liquid, cauliflower, @Tex-Mex paste{1%unit}, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, and 1 1/2 cups water (2 1/2 cups for 4 servings) into #pot{} with veggies.

Bring to a simmer, then cover and reduce heat to medium low. Cook until cauliflower is tender and soup has thickened slightly, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> TIP: If soup isn't thick enough, cook until it reaches desired consistency. If soup seems too thick, add a splash more water.

Taste and season with @salt{} (we used 1 1/2 tsp; 2 1/2 tsp for 4 servings) and @pepper{}.

Pick @cilantro{¼%ounce}(leaves picked from stems) leaves from stems.

Divide soup between bowls and sprinkle with cilantro. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} on the side.